inn1.comm: Well outside the offstump, hint of movement away. left alone

Simmons debut ends in a tragedy. He lasted just two balls. He was tempted by a good-length delivery in that channel, poked at it with an open-face of the bat and the resultant edge was picked up by Akmal low to his right.
Length-delivery just outside the offstump, pushed towards cover
West Indies get off the mark. A short of length delivery, just outside the offstump, Ganga pushes it to left of point
trying to angle it across, ends up pushing it bit too much and it sails harmlessly well outside the offstump
And again. Gayle, removes his bat from the line, lets it go through to Akmal.
on the leg and middle, full in length, tickled to left of square leg
a outswinger in the channel, left alone
around the offstump line, on a length, Ganga pushes forward, places the ball towards cover, thinks about a single but decides against it
The ODI dab shot to thirdman is out. Ganga let the ball swing, waited before tapping it to thirdman
outside the offstump, slightly short of length, angling across, Gayle initially shaped up to play a shot but pulls out at the last minute

What a start for Pakistan! Chris Gayle falls. Big wicket. Full and it swung in a bit, Gayle pushes at it defensively, but ends up pushing the bat inside the line, and the outside edge flew low to the left of Inzamam at first slip and he gobbled it up. It was a outswinger to the right-hand bat, and Gayle spotted it and played it accordingly but this one didn't swing in so much as he anticipated and hence he ended up playing in the wrong line.
Gul pings the length, just outside the off stump. It jags back in and raps Ganga on the pads but the impact was outside the offstump

Big appeal but turned down. Hmm.. Again Gul brought the ball back in from just outside the offstump and Ganga pushed out to defend. The ball beat the intended prod and rapped him on the pad. The point of impact was on the offstump line..
beaten. Careless slash to a fullish-delivery in the zone outside the offstump.
And again. Ganga flirts and its a almost fatal. The ball just whizzes past the outside edge
down the legside, wide called
Almost a mix-up. Ganga pushes a length-delviery to extra cover, sets off, but Samuels sends him back. Ganga makes back in time. No damage done
In the zone outside off, left alone
gets this one to swing away from the right-hander - Ganga is sucked forward, more of a defensive prod, ball clips the edge and races away to third man
good length delivery on the stumps, played with soft hands and the ball rolls away towards mid-off
beaten - so what's new. short of a good length and shaping away, excellent line and length and Samules was clueless, ball zips past the outside edge
left alone outside the off stump, the ball is moving around a bit and Ganga is better off in the Test mode
this one nipped back in sharply and Ganga gets hit on the pad - again bat nowhere near the ball, impact was well outside the line of the off stump and he lives on
Gul is mixing it up nicely here - pushed one way outside the off stump, the awayswinger and Ganga goes after. once again the ball rips past the outside edge
and the one that comes back in. Gul is making full use of the conditions - Ganga once again fails to get bat to ball and is hit on the pad.
defended watchfully
left alone outside the off stump - safe shot
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended down to mid-off
again watchfully defended - no room for a single there
forced away into the gap between mid-off and cover, quick single added to the total
good length delivery, way down the leg side
pushed away towards gully and they scamper through for a single, Hafeez's shy at the stumps misses the stumps at the bowler's end and few extra runs are given away - sloppy
good length delivery outside the off stump, defended
and the sucker ball - wide and shaping away a touch, Samuels plays away from his body and the ball goes through to the keeper
right on the money again. Lands on a length, just outside off, comes in a touch and Ganga pushes forward in defense. Gets a inside-edge and the ball lodges on the pads
beaten. Gul teases Ganga outside the offstump
And again. This one bounces from short of length, moves away and Ganga again pushes his bat, away from his body
Gul continues to torment the batsmen, this time it is Samuels. Just outside the offstump,, he  is not sure whether the ball would cut back in or hold its line , this one holds and he is beaten
Ganga breaks free with a cut over point. Short and wide, and he slashed it over the offside ring
corrects the line and length, in the zone outside off, left alone
nice shape, lands on a length, just outside the offstump, and swings away a touch. Ganga, anctipating more swing, drove outside the line and is beaten
Change of pace. Slower delivery and Ganga doesn't spot it but it drifts down the leg side
just outside the offstump, fullish, pushed to cover point
short of length, outside the offstump, bit of width, Ganga drives on the up but finds the cover fielder
full and on the legs, tickled to long-leg.
full, Ganga drives, gets an outside edge, the ball goes all along the ground, past the third slip, out to thirdman
on the stumps, Samuels gets behind the line, pushes it down the track
pings the short of length, just outside the offstump, defended off the back foot

Awesome shot. Just short of length, outside the offstump and Samuels goes back and across, stands tall to punch it on the rise, past cover point. The running between the wickets was poor and they get just two
Lovely comeback from the bowler. Slightly short of length, just outside off, and this one veers away after landing, Samuels pushes at it and is beaten
Outswinger and Ganga drives but meets air as the ball shapes away from the outside edge.
this one doesn't swing that much and Ganga runs it down to thirdman region
in the zone outside off, Samuels goes back and across to get behind the line, pushes the ball to the offside. No chance of a run
goes for the surprise bouncer, ends up just going down leg as Samuels ducks. Wide called
outside the offstump, short in length, steered to point
this time Samuels pings the gap between cover and point and gets a single.
lands on a length, outside off, shapes away, left alon e
slightly short of length, outside the off, Samuels goes back, steers it to point

not much movement this time. straight outside off, Samuels, who is making every effort to get as much close to the line as possible - at times ends up outside off, gets behind that to push it to cover
around the off and middle, tapped back down the track
on the offstump line, Samuels gets behind it and another dot ball results
on the hips, Samuels goes back and across, works it past square-leg and this time the running is good, they get two
Ambitious swipe to a fullish-delivery outside off, the outside edge takes the ball out to thirdman
outswinger to start off. Swings too early in its trajectory though. Left alone without any fuss
swing and a miss. This time it starts to swing slightly late and Samuels goes hunting outside off.
Full, almost at the blockhole, on the off and middle, stabbed away to the on side
Shoaib Malik does an acrobatic stop at covers. Samuels drives a overpitched-delivery to left of Malik who dives full-length to make the stop
in the zone outside off, pushed to the off side
Gui goes for the bouncer, Samuels goes for the hook but doens't get a touch and AKmal gathers it
drifting just down the legside, attempted glance but doesn't connect. Wide called
short of length, outside off, Samuels rocks back, punches on the up, straight to mid-off
kicks up from short of length, around the offstump line, Samuels punches it on the up but straight to cover
dropped! speared in full and fast, Samuels tries to ping it past mid-on, gets a leading edge  which takes the ball to right of Gul. He stretches his right hand out but can't hold it. Tough chance
full and outside off, Samuels goes for a big drive, top-hand comes out of the bat-handle, ends up driving outside the line and is beaten.
full and on the leg and middle, ends up drifting further down and Ganga is rapped on the pads as he tries to flick.
outside edge again.  Ganga throws his bat at a fullish-delivery outside off that swings away late and the thirdman moves to his left to make the stop. That's Abdul Razzaq down there&
Swat! Just short of length, outside the offstump, the length and line giving opportunity for Ganga to biff it past cover
fuller, teasing line and length, Ganga takes his bat out of the line, lets it go through to the 'keeper
This time he couldn't hold himself back. Goes in search of a wide one outside off, can't get a touch.

appeal for lbw. Was there a inside edge. Full and on the middle, Ganga goes for one of his airy drives where no contact is made with the ball and is rapped on the pads. There must have been an inside edge
short of length, pushed to cover
outswinger on the offstump line, Samuels gets behind the line, pushes out in defense
this one starts off from outside off, another outswinger, left alone. Now will he bring the next ball back in?
He tries. Ends up going straight on the middle stump line, Samuels tries to whip it across the line, doesn't get a touch and is rapped on the thigh pad
slightly slower in pace, outside the offstump, Samuels lets it go
hones in on the offstump line, defended off the front foot
Full and on the offstump line, Ganga, unlike Samuels, likes to go on the front foot, towards the ball, pushes it down the track
appeal for lbw. Going down. Full and it drifts in, attempted flick shot doesn't connect
this one climbs up from a length, catches Ganga by surprise but he adjusts by taking the bottom-hand out of the bat-handle, taps it close on the on side
short and outside off, Ganga goes for the cut, gets an under edge and it bounds off to the right of AKmal
full, straight on the middle, bat comes around the front pad, in time, and gets it down to long-leg
comes in with the angle, on the leg and middle, tickled behind squareleg
And again. this time Ganga works it in front of squareleg
banged in short, climbs up chest high, just outside off, Samuels is caught in a tangle, gets too close to the line, stabs at it, gets an inside edge that takes the ball close to the offstump.
short of length, pushed to cover point
slower one, full in length on the offstump line, pushed away to on side
If only runs were given for effort, Ganga would have got a four here. He leans forwar, then swivels,, goes for a pull but doesn't get much wood behind the leather.
full, on the legs, should have been put away but Samuels pings the square-leg fielder. No run. Runrate : 2.13 runs per over
Samuels gets his offdrive out, manages to ping the gap between the bowler and mid-off. Does't time it well though
fullish, on the offstump line, Ganga drives uppishly but it falls short of mid-off
Overpitched, Ganga drives, again uppishly, it hovers in the air close to Gul, at midoff, who is bit late in reacting. He ends up diving but can't get his palm under the ball.
full in length, defended off the front foot
in the zone outside off, left alone
overpitched, outside off, driven straight to mid-off
full, on the off and middle, driven to mid-on
just outside offstump, on a length, pushed to cover
Finally Samuels breaks free. Times his drive well. Overpitched and he drives past the bowler.
outside off, run down to thirdman
short of length, outside off, steered to point

Gotcha! Serves up one full and on the leg and middle, it shapes away a touch and Ganga ends up trying to whip across the line. He gets a leading edge which takes the ball straight into the waiting palms of Inzy at cover.
on the legs, tucked to fine-leg. For some reason Samuels thinks there is two in that, turns blind, Lara sends him back and he makes back just in time.
Goes for a drive, too early into his stroke, gets an inside edge which takes the ball to mid-on
slanted across the offstump, left alone
full, on the legs, Lara gets behind the line, whips it but can't beat squareleg
Huge appeal for lbw. Ball lands just outside legstump line, comes in with the angle and Lara ends up pushing outside the line. Is struck in line but the ball had landed outside leg.
in the zone outside off, left alone
similar to the ball that led to a lbw appeal, but this time Lara gets behind the line, pushes it to the offside
Overpitched on the leg and mdidle, Samuels stands up tall, punches it down the ground between the bowler and mid-on
almost a run out. A very quick single taken. On the middle and leg, tickled to squareleg, Imran Farhat swooped in on the ball, had a shy, misses but Lara had made his crease
That whiplash squaredrive is out. Lara leans forward, drives it past poitn
on the offstump line, pushed to cover, Lara wants a run but decides against it
length-delivery on the off, steered to point
on the offstump line, leans forward, opens the face of the bat, pushes it to cover point
full on the middle and leg, Samuels stands tall, drives pleasingly to right of mid-on
on the stumps, on a length, Lara goes back rather than moving forward, ends up stabbing at it, manages to put bat on ball, keeps it away
full, driven to cover
quickish spin, starts off from outside off, left alone
just outside off, not much spin, left alone
slightly slower, again outside off, again not that much spin, padded away
delivered from wide of the wickets, lands in on a length around off, turns away, dabbed to point
81.9kph. around the offstump line, flatish, slight turn, pushed to the offside
arm-ball on the off and middle, Samuels shuffles across, taps it to the on side for a single. Rehman gets across, makes the stop and has a shy at the non-striker's end
down the leg side, brushes the pad enroute to AKmal
angles in from outside off, full in length, Samuels leans forward, pushes out in defense
slightly short in length, on the middle, the length allows Samuels to tap it across the line but cant' beat squareleg
fuller, on the middle. worked to midwicket
overpitched on the legs, flicked through the midwicket-gap but the heavy outfield means they will get just two runs
floated on the offstump line, worked to  midwicket, with the spin
outside the offstump, flat and comes in with the angle, dabbed to point
floats in from around the wickets, Samuels goes back, tickles it to midwicket region
turns in from outside off, pushed to cover
Lara wants to work it to on side, doesn't turn enough, the ball goes to offside
just outside off, turns in, Lara goes back, cuts it late. Lovely shot.
pitched up outside the off stump and Lara finds the fielder at cover point

short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line. Ball stopped a bit after hitting the deck. Lara looking to forces it away on the off stump ends up with a thick edge but the ball goes straight into the ground on the off side
forced away off the back-foot to the cover region, again no run
left alone outside the off stump
another one stops a bit after hitting the deck and Lara almost ends up playing it back to Razzaq
boundary - that's a rare sight, driven away through the gap midwicket and mid-on, Gul with the slide helps the ball over the ropes
defended on the front-foot
worked away for an easy single
line and length delivery, defended on the back-foot - very defensive shot
tapped away towards gully, fielder moves across quickly and cuts off the single
played away towards short midwicket
once again Rehman hits the right length but this time Lara gets it away well wide of the fielder at gully and they stroll across for a single
pitched up outside the off stump, fuller in length but Lara plays safe - forces it away wide of the fielder at mid-off and a quick single is added to the total
on the middle and off stump line, defended watchfully

DISASTER! worked away off the pads to the short midwicket region. Not sure if there was a run on there - Lara certainly thought so but Samuels stood his ground. Malik moved across to his left and quickly passed the ball to Razzak and rest as they say is history - Lara had given up well before the ball had reached Razzak
on the stumps, defended
full and wide outside the off stump - probably the slower delivery gone wrong. Samuels picks it up early and drills it through cover
defended towards gully
on the stumps and Smith forces it away towards point

Rehman opens his account in ODIs and West Indies sink further - tossed up delivery, on the stumps and it straightened after hitting the track - Smith playing for the spin pushes forward to defend and the ball hits the pad in line with the stumps. The only doubt was if the ball hit the pad first.  Aleem Dar there was quicker than a trigger-happy American cop.
defended on the front-foot
flat delivery - driven away towards cover point - end of a successful over, one that Rehman will remember for a long time
good length delivery, driven straight to the fielder at cover
fraction short and on the middle and leg stump line, Samuels shuffles across a bit and works it away towards midwicket for a single
tight line and length, defended on the front-foot. Solid shot but ...
punched down to mid-on - early call and a quick single is added to the total
driven down to long-on, easy single
driven back to the bowler
width offered outside the off stump and Samuels cuts it away in the air to the fielder at gully - almost carried
defended with a straight bat and the ball rolls back to the bowler
gone! slightly short and turning away. Samuels goes back and slashes hard at it, ball clips the outside edge, ricochets off the keeper's glove and goes straight to Younis Khan at first slip
driven straight back to the bowler
tossed up outside the off stump, driven away towards short cover
tossed up and turning away, driven away with the spin to the cover region - another good over cover to an end.
short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line and Morton taps it away towards cover
good length delivery and this one nipped back in after hitting the deck, Morton pushes forward and defends, bat and pad held together
played away off the back-foot to the cover region - again no room for a single there
full and on the stumps and Morton hammers it straight back past the bowler to the long-on fence
pitched up outside the off stump. Morton goes right back and punches it back to the bowler - again presented the full face of the bat there
turning away nicely - Ramdin pulls away late
tossed up and this one lands full outside the off stump, driven straight to the fielder at cover
in the channel and turning away. Ramdin leaves it through to the keeper
worked away through square leg for an easy single
worked away with the spin to the point region
fraction short, punched off the back-foot to the long-off region. Easy single to end the over
tossed up outside the off stump, defended on the back-foot
driven away through point for an easy single
defended plunging forward
worked away on the leg side
fuller length delivery outside the off stump, driven straight back to the bowler
driven down to long-on for a single
channel delivery, driven down to long-off for a single
pitched outside the off stump and turning away, Morton reads it well and leaves it through to the keeper
tossed up on the middle and off stump line, Morton gets a good stride in and defends it with a straight bat
driven away straight to the fielder at point
bit of width offered outside the off stump. Morton leans back and drives it away through cover point for a single
tossed up, once again the ball grips the sruface and turns away from the right-hander. Ramdin goes for the cut and is beaten by a long way
turned away off the pads to the square leg region
driven down to long-on - yet another easy single added to the total
worked away against the spin to the square leg region
defended on the back-foot and the ball rolls away towards short cover
once again tucked away through the vacant square leg region
the one that goes straight on and Ramdin is hit on the pad - appeal for lbw turned down
bowled from round the stumps - pitched in line and turning away, Morton leaves it for the keeper
driven away off the back-foot and the ball goes past the DIVING Inzi at cover
two more. on and around the leg stump line - Morton waits for the ball and wristfully turns it away through midwicket
defended on the back-foot and the ball rolls away towards point
wide outside the off stump and Morton takes it on the pad - half hearted appeal turned down
swept away nicely to the fine leg region
comes down the track to the pitch of the delivery and drives it down to long-on for a single
100 comes up - tossed up on the middle and off stump line, Ramdin goes right across the stumps and scoops it down to fine leg for a brace - cheeky
this one turns in sharply and Ramdin looking to cut it away is cramped for room - jams his bat down in time and the ball rolls away towards point
pushed away towards cover
driven down to long-on - came well forward to meet the ball
forced away square on the off side and they scamper through for a single
goes for the cut and gets beaten by a long way
defended on the front-foot
goes right back and plays it away towards point
tossed up and turning away - Morton gets well forward and defends it down on the off side
played straight to Inzi at cover, excellent over so far
driven away off the back-foot to the deep cover region
full and on the pads, driven straight to the fielder at midwicket
good length delivery, ball kept low after hitting the deck but Morton some home manages to squeeze it away towards midwicket - Malik is the fielder there
off-cutter - way outside the off stump and Morton straight bats it past the bowler to the long-off fence - powerful shot
excellent comeback - in the block-hole and Morton jams his bat down in time
low fulltoss on the pads, hint of reverse swing there. Morton looking to slog it away towards midwicket fails to make contact and the ball hits him on the thigh
bit short - cut away off the back-foot to the point region
tossed up and turning away from middle and off - Ramdin drives, lazy looking shot and the ball spins past the outside edge
punched off the back-foot to the cover region.
short and turning away - Ramdin goes right back and cuts it away through the gap between cover and point. Sweeper moves across in the deep and keeps it down to just one
on the stumps, Morton goes for the sweep and the ball rolls away off the pad
cut away off the back-foot to deep cover and that's the end of a fantastic spell on debut. 10.0-2-20-2
high fulltoss - drifting down the leg side, surprise delivery and Morton was all at sea, ball hits him on the thigh pad and rolls down to short fine leg - bit of inside edge involved i guess
pitched up outside the off stump, driven hard but straight to the fielder at mid-on
off-cutter. Ramdin gets behind the line and defends it down on the leg side
pitched up on the middle and leg stump line - hint of reverse swing. Ramdin almost falls over trying to drive it away - ball goes straight to the fielder at midwicket
well disguised slower delivery and Ramdin picks it up late
fulltoss down the leg side, Ramdin hammers it with the swing and the ball sails over the long-leg fence. Horrible delivery put away in style.
comes down the track and drives it straight to the fielder at midwicket. failed to get to the pitch of the delivery but Morton adjusted well in the end
pitched close to the off stump line and turning in - Morton goes right back and plays it away towards midwicket
worked away with the spin and the get it well in front of square leg - takes on Razzak in the deep and comfortably makes it back for the second - excellent running between the wickets
defended down to silly mid-on
lofted away towards long-on - Rahman swoops in from the deep but fails to hold on to a fairly easy chance - that's poor cricket from the young man.
turned away towards short fine leg
full and on the stumps, bit of reverse swing there - Ramdin taps it away towards midwicket
drifting down the leg side - too quick fro Ramdin and the ball rolls away off the pad
short of a good length delivery, this one nipped back in a long way. Morton awkwardly plays it away towards gully and they scamper through for a single
driven away towards midwicket and they cross over for a quick single  - throw came in at the bowler's end but was nowhere near the target
in-dipper and Morton is beaten by the angle - ball hits the pad and rolls away on the off side
full and drifting down the leg side - another swing and a miss
tossed up on the stumps, Ramdin makes room and taps it away behind point for a single
slow and short - Morton rocks back and pulls it away with the spin to the midwicket fence. Excellent placement
worked away wide of the fielder at short fine leg
fuller in length, driven straight back down the track to the long-on region - they need boundaries
yorker and Mortons ends up playing it back to the bowler
turned away straight to the fielder at short fine leg. End of an excellent over from the off-spinner
pressure? horrible ball down the leg side

played away through midwicket. Ramdin calls for the second and sprints across - Umar Gul hurtles across in the deep and fires in a brilliant throw at the striker's end - Akmal moves in front of the stumps, collects the ball cleanly and drags it into the stumps.&
driven off the back-foot to the cover region
fraction short - pulled away to deep midwicket
defended on the back-foot and the ball rolls away on the off side - quick single take
good length delivery on the stumps and Morton slogs it away to the wide long-on fence
swing and a miss outside the off stump
short rising delivery on the middle and off stump line, Bradshaw leans back and runs it down to third man - Morton wanted a second but Bradshaw was unmoved
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Morton swings across the line eyeing the midwicket fence - ball clips the inside edge and rolls away well in front of square leg
thumping drive but the ball goes straight to the fielder at mid-off
short of a good length, was the slow leg-cutter. Bradshaw looking to run it down to third man fails to make contact and the ball goes through to the keeper
full and straight - Bradshaw is beaten for pace and the ball hits him on the pad. Loud appeal for lbw turned down - probably pitched outside leg

tapped away towards backward point and they scamper through for a single - Hafeez moves in quickly, the pick-up is spot on and he hits the bowler's stumps with clinical precision - Bradshaw is history
driven down to long-on for a single
swing and a miss outside the off stump
driven down to long-on, again just a single

gone! well disguised slower delivery. Morton never picked it up - swipes across the line, ball clips the top edge and spoons up towards midwicket. Younis Khan nicely settles under it - West Indies nine down
full and on the stumps, driven straight back to the bowler
good length delivery, driven straight to the fielder at cover
yorker outside the off stump - 84 mph and Collymore is beaten outside the off stump
full and straight - punched away towards cover for a single
Taylor comes down the track even before the ball is delivered - Gul drags it short and Taylor had no chance of getting bat on ball

all over! full and on the middle and off stump line - Taylor walks across the stumps in an effort to scoop it down to fine leg but misses the target by miles and the ball crashes into the stumps. Done and dusted in 49.5 overs - well done Pakistan

inn2.comm: Taylor produces a Harmison special. Way down the leg side.
Taylor strikes! Fabulous outswinger. Full and inviting a drive, Hafeez obliged but the ball left him late and took with it , a bit of outside edge.
And almost repeats it. This one landed just short of driveable length, Akmal resisted a drive and lets the ball go through to the 'keeper
goes for the dream outswinger. Starts off from leg and middle and tries to swing it from there, dream doesn't turn to reality, Akmal pings long leg
full, on the middle, hint of in swing, Imran Farhat goes for a drive, bit ambitious, is beaten by the swing and the inside edge takes the ball to midwicket
Full, too full, outside off, square-driven to deep point. Akmal comes on strike
Again Taylor tries to start his outswing from leg or probably it could be due to the left-right batting combo, flicked away through midwicket
drifting down the leg side. Umpire Harper extends his arm
fullish, on the offstump line, leans forward to defend it towards cover
angles in on the middle and leg, flicked to the gap in midwicket
full, slanted across, driven to cover
short of length, around the off stump line, he stabs at it, gets an inside edge which takes the ball to shortish fineleg
What a peach of a delivery. Landed on a length, around off, forcing Akmal to play before leaving him in lurch.
full, on the middle, driven down the track, back to the bowler
overpitched, around the offstump line, squaredriven and Morton gets across quickly from point, makes a tumbling stop to his right
worked to right of Lendl Simmons at square-leg who dives to his right to make a neat stop. West Indies are fielding sharply here.
slanted across, Farhat opens the bat-face, steers it to point where Dwayne Smith makes the stop
lands on a length, angles across, Akmal leans forward, head over the ball, taps it close on the offside. Completely behind the line there.
slightly short in length, outside the off, steered to Smith at point
short of length, around the leg and middle stump line, comes in with the angle. pushed to midwicket
fuller, around the offstump line, Akmal leans forward, pushes it towards cover. Pakistan have all the time in the world, the focus would be to preserve the wickets against the new ball.
short, rises almost chest high, around that offstump line, Akmal stands tall, taps it down, towards point
on the leg and middle, slanted across, Farhat works his wrist overtime, sends it across the line to squarleg where Simmons makes the stop
full and around the offstump line, driven to mid off
short of length, on the middle, Farhat tries to whip it across, ends up pushing it towards right of square-leg, the ball rolls slowly and gives enough time to get across for a single
banged in short, rears up at the ribs, Akmal gets on top of the bounce, keeps the ball down. Well played
full and on the leg and middle, goes on with the angle, Akmal flicks it behind squareleg
Again he drifts down legside, Akmal allows the ball to come in, glances it fine.
in the zone outside off, Farhat leans forward, opens the bat-face, steers it to point
Full length ball, pushed to cover
Back of a length this time. Typical Bradshaw length. Farhat rocks back and pushes it to mid-off
Farhat announces his intentions by dancing down the track but Bradshaw fires it towards his pads. The ball richochets off his pads to the right of the wicketkeeper.
Wide ball this time. Farhat throws the kitchen sink at it and the thick edge flies past second slip for a streaky four
Nudged to short fine leg
Short and wide, Akmal lashes it hard and it falls short of the cover fielder. Misfield allows for an easy single
Straight and full from Taylor, arhat tries to flick it but misses. Huge appeal for lbw but Aleem Dar declines. Replays suggest that the ball might have gone above the stumps
Ducked a short ball
Down legside
Pushed to cover
lands on a length, on the middle and leg, goes on with the angle, flicked to square-leg
slightly slower, full in length, around the offstump line, Akmal goes for a drive but is slightly thrown off by the lack of pace, the ball rolls back to the bowler
fuller, on the off, Akmal drives it to cover
drifting on to the legs, Akmal shuffles inside, flicked to long-leg
on the middle and leg, tucked to squareleg
drifts down the legside, they go up in appeal, must have brushed the pads
Aha. A very nice pleasing off drive. Mind you... it was overpitched, but Farhat leant forward fully and presented the full face of the bat.
drags back the length, punched to cover
short and wide, Farhat goes for a horizontal stroke, doesn't pack much punch nor places it and it goes straight to point
almost dragged back to the stumps. Goes for a drive, away from his body, and it rolls back to his pads and rolls past the offstump
full and slanted across, Farhat moves forward, lands his front foot on the heels - not the ideal way, should try to plant the toe- covers the line well though and sends it back to the bowler
bouncer and ducked under without much fuss
full and on the middle, comes in with the angle, Akmal stays back, gets his bat down in time, ahead of his pads, keeps the ball away
lands outside off, on a length, holds its line, run down to thirdman.
another delvery that straightened after landing on the middle. Farhat is anticipating the one that slants away, shapes to drive to cover, is cramped up a bit but adjust to push it down the track
full and well outside the off, Farhat reaches out for it, well away from the body, wrists it away square and it flies to the right of point. Risky shot
in the zone outside off, good testing delivery after that previous one, but Farhat lets this one go through to the 'keeper
full, around the offstump line, pushed to cover
right on the money. Hones in on the offstump line, short of length, Akmal goes back, punches it to cover
good teasing delivery, just outside the off, an uncertain Akmal stabs at it, and the ball runs off the outside edge to thirdman
length-delivery around off, Farhat stands tall, punches it on the up, towards mid-off

Gone! That fatal flirt outside off from Farhat. Time and again that swish has led to his demise. Short in length and slanted across, Farhat throws his bat at it, the ball flies off the outer edge to right of second slip, Good sharp catch. Collymore strikes for West Indies.
full, on middle and leg, going with the angle, pushed to the on side
this one holds its line after landing on a length around the offstump line and Younis is in a bit of trouble as he pushes hard at it. The ball gets the inside edge, crashes on to his pads
A single to thirdman
on the middle, full in length, Younis gets behind the line, offers the full face of the bat in defense
on the legs, flicked past squareleg
Keeper standing up but a bad ball. drifting down leg. Younis waits for it to arrive, tickles it fine and Bradshaw makes a good stop, with his right boot, near the ropes
gentle outswinger, Younis leans forward, covers the stumps, shoulders arms
another outside edge, another single in that region between point and thirdman
full, just outside off, Younis thrusts his left foot forward, drives to cover
full and on the off and middle, defended off the back foot
lands on a length, cuts back in bit, Younis adjusts, tucks it to square-leg. Oohs and aahs from Collymore as he thought it was going to strike the pad
drags back the length, lands on a good length, moves the ball in, Akmal leans forward in defense
fullish, outside off, driven to Lara at mid-off
pitches on a length, moves back in a touch, pushed to cover point
fuller, just outside off, defended towards cover
length-delivery, on the offstump line, Younis gets behind the line, to push it back down the track
slightly short in length, outside off, punched to cover point.
drifts down the legside, wide called
length-delivery, around the offstump line, Akmal goes for a cover drive, plays too early, gets an inside edge that takes the ball to midwicket
well outside off, holds its line, Akmal lets that one go through to Ramdin
length-delivery on the off, Akmal goes back, pushes it to cover. Solid as a rock ... Akmal. Pleasing technique.
on the middle and leg, goes on with the angle, worked to midwicket
length-delivery, outside off, Akmal leans forward, defends it towards cover.
double strike by Collymore! Akmal falls. The commentators curse! Just when I was talking him up, he reaches out for a delivery, slashes it straight to Smith at backward point
length-delivery outside off, Younis drives to mid-off
short of length, around offstump, not much pace which allows Younis to stand tall and whip it through the midwicket gap
wide one outside off stump, Younis couldn't reach it.
short of length, just outside off, played to cover
fullish, outside off, driven past the bowler, Smith gets a hand, and the ball rolls towards midoff
length-delivery, outside off, driven to mid-off
fullish, on the off, Inzamam drives, gets a leading edge to mid-off
short of length, around the offstump line, Inzamam stands tall, punches it to cover point
short of length, just outside the offstump, Inzy moves close to the line, punches it to point
again outside off, Inzamam moves towards the ball, drives to cover
on the off, moves in a touch, Inzamam has to play around his front pad, to squareleg
length-delivery, just outside off, Inzamam goes for a drive on the up, doesnt make contact and it raps him on the pad. Collymore appeals but it is well outside off
short of length, landed on the leg stump line, moves in, shovelled to midwicket
fullish, outside off, slanting away, pushed to cover
slanted across again, Inzy leans forward, defends
length-delivery, just outside off, pushed back to the bowler
lands on a length, around the middle, goes away with the angle, Inzy shuffles across, ends up almost at the offstump, pushes the ball, now on his hips, towards midwicket
fuller, on the middle, this time Inzy doesn't move sideways, stays, pushes it to wards mid-off.
blistering cover drive! Reaches out to a fullish delivery outside off, drills it through cover. Super shot
full and around off, pushed back to the bowler
almost dragged back to the stumps. Length-delivery outside off, Younis throws his bat at it, gets an inside edge...
fuller, around off, holds its line, Younis plays inside the line a touch, pushes it to cover
short in length, outside off, punched to cover
fuller, outside off, pushed to cover
slanted across, full in length, pushed back down the track
slanted across, full in length, swing and a miss
short and Inzamam goes for a pull. Doesn't connect well, ends up shovelling it to mid-on
pings the zone outside off, moves away after landing on a length, left alone
full and on the legs, tickled to squareleg
defended off the front foot
outside off, shapes away after landing, left alone
on the offstump line, comes in a touch, defended on the front foot
outside off, partly edged, partly steered, to the thirdman region
slower offbreak, on the middle, moves away, edged to point
Shocker! Big wide . ends up almost in the first slip.
on the middle, Younis gets behind the line to defend
just a touch outside off, steered to point
on the middle and off, full in length, drawing him forward, Younis leans forward to push it to the offside
just on the offstump line, punched past point
Inzamam gets off the mark. Finally. Runs a fullish-ball outside off, down to thirdman
good length delivery, drifting onto middle and aleg, driven away towards short fine leg. Excellent diving effort from Simmons saves few runs
again the middle and leg stump line, driven wide of the fielder at midwicket and they scamper through for a single
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven down to mid-off
short of a good length delivery, in the channel outside the off stump. Inzi walks back and across - gets right behind the line and defends it with a straight bat
another tight delivery, driven with a straight bat and the ball finds the fielder at mid-off
excellent line and length - Inzi was caught in two minds there - whether to play forward or back, in the end he plunges forward and drives it down to mid-off
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Khan plays away from his body and ends up with an inside edge and the ball rolls away behind the stumps
short and wide outside the off stump - Khan waits for the ball and slaps it through the gap between slip and gully - good shot to break the ice
good length delivery, no shot offered
drifting down the leg side and the ball rolls away off the pad to the square leg region, easy single
full and on the pads, driven wide off the fielder at midwicket and they sprint across for a single - Inzi was quick off the blocks and he made it across comfortably - a rare sight
defended outside the off stump
on the middle and leg stump line, played down to silly mid-on
fraction short and Inzi goes for the pull - went hard at it and the ball rolls away off the inner half of the bat
in the channel outside the off stump, defended watchfully
drifting down the leg side, can't afford to bowl such deliveries
driven off the back-foot to the mid-on region, again not timed to perfection and the ball rolled away off the inner half of the bat
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven straight to the fielder at cover
off-cutter. Came back in sharply - Inzi plunges forward to defend and gets hit on the pad, Loud appeal for lbw turned down - impact was clearly outrside the line of the off stump
and again - Smith beats Inzi with the off-cutter. once again the impact was well outside the line of the off stump and the appeal is duly turned down
worked away from middle and leg - gets it through midwicket for a brace
defended down to mid-off and Inzi sprints across for a single. excellent running between the wickets
pitched up on the pads. Khan leans well forward and drives it into the gap between mid-on and midwicket.
defended down on the leg side
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven straight to the fielder at cover
shot! fuller length delivery outside the off stump, Khan gets forward in a flash and drills it through the gap between mid-off and cover.  Excellent placement

and he throws his wicket away - short ball, excellent surprise delivery. Younis Khan goes for the pull and the top edge spoons up behind the stumps on the leg side - Ramdin calls for it and nicely settles under it. That's the breakthrough they were looking for - game on here.
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven straight to the fielder at cover
full and on the pads - attempted yorker and Inzi clips it away to fine leg for a single
driven straight to the fielder at cover
cut away off the back-foot. forced away well wide of the fielder at point
flicked away off the wicket to the midwicket region - Malik off the mark
horrible delivery - way down the leg side and that's a wide. Smith kicks the ground in frustration
on the middle and leg stump line, tucked away nicely to fine leg for a single
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven straight to the man at cover
turned away through midwicket, yet another easy single added to the total
on the pads, turned straight to the fielder at midwicket - no single there
short and angling across the right-hander. Malik waits for the ball and cuts late - Taylor moves across quickly in the deep and cuts off the boundary
turned away towards midwicket
angled into the pads and the Malik turns it away through square leg for a brace

and gone! short of a good length delivery, pitched outside the off stump and angling across. Malik searches for it like a man diagonally parked in a parallel universe. Looked as if he was trying to find the gap between keeper and first slip. For the record the edge went straight to Ramdin behind the stumps.
bouncer - pitched outside the off stump and angling in - Razzak ducks under it.
left alone outside the off stump
short of a good length and in the channel outside the off stump - Inzi watchfully leaves it through to the keeper
makes room and cuts hard - straight to the fielder at cover
full and on the stumps, punched straight to the fielder at acover
drifting down the leg side. Inzi fails to make contact, ball clips the pad and goes through to the keeper
worked away well in front of square leg - As always Inzi is looking well in control
left alone outside the off stump
short of a length and angling across - Inzi leaves it through to the keeper
on the stumps, Inzi gets well forward and drives it down to mid-off
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line. Inzi gets behind the line and defends it with a straight bat
cramped for room outside the off stump but Inzi cuts hard - Smith at backward point fails to stop it cleanly and a single is added to the total
played away towards square leg
short of a good length delivery, ball kept a bit low after hitting the deck but it was too wide outside the off stump to trouble Razzak
make that 59 more to get - way outside the off stump and Inzi leaves it through to the keeper
cut hard but straight to the fielder at point
good length delivery outside the off stump, Inzi waits on the back-foot and at the last moment drives it away straight to the fielder at point
turned away on the leg side. Played with soft hands and they scamper through for a single
good length delivery on the middle and leg stump line, turned away straight to the fielder at square leg
short delivery outside the off stump, the leg-cutter as they call it - Razzaq shuffles across a long way, covers the stumps and leaves it through to the keeper
driven through extra-cover and an easy single is added to the total - 3 runs off the over and that's all they need
ripper of a delivery outside the off stump and Razzaq is turned inside out - ball missed the edge by a whisker
short ball, pulled off the back-foot and the ball rolls away off the bottom edge
cut straight to the fielder at point - Razzaq struggling a bit here
good length delivery, on and around the off stump line - Razzaq gets forward and runs it down to fine leg for a single, nicely opened the face of the bat at the point of impact and got it through
driven away towards cover
on the middle and leg stumps line - Inzi, looking to whip it away through midwicket ends up with a thick edge and the ball rolls down to third man
tossed up on the stumps, driven straight back down the track
pitched outside the off stump and this one turned back in sharply - Inzi pushes forward to defend and gets hit on the pad. Loud appeal turned down. Impact was well wide outside the off stump
beaten outside the off stump - another loud appeal turned down, Gayle is looking good here
worked away with the spin to the square leg region
turned to midwicket
fraction short, Razzaq goes right back and drives it away through the gap between the cover fielders. End of a good first over from Gayle.
punched away off the back-foot to the point region

lucky! good length delivery outside the off stump, ball kept bit low after hitting the stumps. Razzaq drives away from his body and the inside edge races away to the fine leg fence. Missed the off stump by a whisker. Ramdin did his best but ... Welcome runs for Pakistan
defended on the front-foot
turned away towards the vacant square leg region. Easy single added to the total
slower delivery outside the off stump, watchfully played away towards cover
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven away towards cover
tossed up and turning in, defended on the front-foot
excellent ball - this one gripped the surface and turned sharply, Razzaq defends on the back-foot and the ball rolls away behind the stumps on the off side
forced away towards point and a quick single is added to the total
driven down to mid-on
down the leg side
turned away off the back-foot to the square leg region
cut away off the back-foot to the gully region, fielder moves across quickly and negates the chance of a single
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Inzi pushes forward and works it away towards midwicket. bit of a mix-up going for the single and in the end they decide not to go for it
drifting down the leg side. was a free hit but Inzi fails to make contact and the ball rolls away off the pad
short of a good length delivery on the middle and off stump line. Razzaq gets behind the line and presents the full face of the bat
great delivery. pitched in the channel outside the off stump and shaping away - Razzaq was clueless and the ball zips past the outside edge
fraction short - Razzaq gets on top of the bounce and tucks it down to third man for a single
leg-cutter. bit too wide to trouble Inzi
drifting down the leg side, Razzaq fails to cash in
defended outside the off stump
pushed away towards cover point and they sprint across for a single - neatly done
turned away through square leg -  walking single
solid defensive shot - presented the full face of the bat
tossed up outside the off stump, defended on the front-foot
good length delivery on the off stump line, Inzi shuffles across and defends it back down the track
plunges forward to defend and the ball rolls away towards cover, hit the pad first but the impact was well outside the line of the off stump
drifting down the elg side and once again Inzi fails to get bat on ball
lovely delivery, good length and shaping away - Inzi is sucked into the drive and the ball rips past the outside edge
good length delivery and Inzi tamely punches it down to mid-on. Good over so far
and it's a maiden. good length delivery - in the channel outside the off stump and the back-foot drive finds the fielder at cover
Flat and full outside the off stump, Razzaq stretches well forward and drives it away through covers for a couple
another fuller length delivery, this time on the pads and Razzaq turns it away well in front of square leg
fraction short and turning in - Inzi goes right back, making full use of the crease and turns it away through square leg
defended outside the off stump
Razzaq too goes right back and gets the ball through square leg for a single
short and wide - massive chop but the ball finds the fielder at point
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Razzaq defends
edged away towards third man

Collymore! perfect line and length and shaping away from the right-hander - Razzaq goes fishing outside the off stump and catches a thin edge, Ramdin does the rest. Pakistan six down and in deep trouble now.
good delivery first up, defended watchfully
drifting down the leg side and the ball rolls away off the pad
pitched up outside the off stump and Hasan drives it straight to the fielder at mid-off
worked away on the leg side
driven down to long-on
short ball, pulled away to deep midwicket. Again just a single
driven on the bounce and straight to Lara at cover
driven away towards cover - 'yes' and 'no' calls and in the end they decide not to go for the single
tight delivery to end the over. Naved-ul-Hasan gets forward and taps it back to Gayle
short and wide outside the off stump. Inzi rock back and chops it away through the gap between point and gully. bad delivery put away in style and the crowd loves it
under pressure Samuels drags it short and Inzi pulls it away well in front of square leg - four more added to the total.
worked away towards short fine leg
Samuels strikes back! full and on the stumps, Hasan goes back to defend but is beaten by the turn and the ball hits the pad plumb in front of the stumps.
driven away towards point, tight fielding cuts off the single
on the pads and Rehman works it away through the vacant midwicket region and the single will keep him on strike
tossed up outside the off stump and Rehman drives hard - excellent diving stop by Lara at short cover saves runs
another fuller length delivery outside the off stump and this time Rehman gets it past Lara at short cover - 20 more to get
tossed up and turning in, Inzi waits for the ball and defends it down on the leg side

Cometh the Hour, Cometh the Man - loose delivery on the middle and leg stump line. Inzi quickly goes down on one knee and sweeps it past the diving fielder at short fine leg - that's a crucial boundary
worked away towards midwicket - easy single
flat delivery outside the off stump, Rehman gets forward and plays it back to the bowler
short and wide outside the off stump and Inzi cuts it away towards point - diving save stops runs but fails to cut off the single
driven down to mid-off
good length delivery outside the off stump, Rehman gets a good stride in and drives it in the air and just over the fielder at cover - that was close
worked away to short fine leg and they cross over - 11 more need now.
Atrocious. Bradshaw oversteps and Pakistan are just 10 runs away from victory

DROPPED! good length delivery outside the off stump with a hint of away swing at the tail end - Rehman is sucked into the drive and the edge is produced. Ramdin diving away to his left grasses a fairly easy chance - what a mess
driven away towards cover
punched down to long-on and he walks across as if he is having a early morning walk - what a player.
driven on the up towards cover, straight to Lara there
cut away late - diving stop by Smith at short third man saves runs but fails to cut off the single
good length delivery outside the off stump - Inzi walks into the shot and drives it down to long-off - just 6 more needed now
fulltoss on the pads and Rehman punches it down to wide long-on
almost! short of a good length delivery, in the channel and slanting away - Rehman plays inside the line and the ball zips past the outside edge
short rising delivery on the stumps. Rehman gets right on top of the bounce and defends it down into the track. Well played - Inzi walks down the track and has a word with the youngester
short delivery outside the off stump and Rehman leaves it through to the keeper - setting him up for the fuller one?
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, played away towards point

good length delivery, pitched outside the off stump and slanting across - Rehman looking to defend it on the back-foot ends up with a thick edge. Ramdin dives across to his left and takes a good catch.
good length delivery outside the off stump, Rao gets well forward and punches it away through cover point.
good length delivery, turning in - Rao gets forward and defends it with a straight bat
full and on the stumps, punched down to mid-on
tossed up outside the off stump, Rao drives well  - diving stop by the fielder at cover cuts off the single. Tension mounts and the crowd is dead silent
drifting down the leg side, Rao fails to make contact and the ball rolls away off the pad
driven straight to the fielder at midwicket
not again! quicker delivery outside the off stump and the edge rolls away well wide of the fielder at gully.
good length delivery on the pads and Rao neatly turns it away towards fine leg for a single.

and Inzi finishes it off it style - short delivery on the middle and leg stump line, Inzi rocks back and pulls it away well wide of the fielder at short fine leg. There is no protection in the deep and the ball rolls over the ropes - crowd goes berzerk
